frameDefinitions: A Perceiver briefly perceives a Phenomenon, often resulting in partial or uncertain perception.
This scenario describes a series of Events, associated with a single Participant, i.e., the history of the Participant.
An Agent causes an Impactor to make sudden, forcible contact with an Impactee, or manipulates two (or more)
An Entity that is previously not visible to a Perceiver becomes visible.
An Entity exists at a particular Location, at a particular Time, as observed by an implicit observer.
An Entity is understood to be experienceable within a particular set of delimited Circumstances, which may be more narrowly expressed by a Time, Place.
frameExamples: I 've been waiting here to catch a <t>glimpse</t> of the snow leopard for seven hours.
We've been worried about our recent hire's <t><fex name='Events'>history</fex></t> of deceiving employers.
He <t>slammed</t> his fist down on the table and bellowed something unintelligible.
The armada <t>appeared</t> on the horizon at sunset.
Liquid water was <t>present</t> on the surface of Mars billions of years ago.
This type of behavior <t>occurs</t> in several primate mating rituals.
listRoleDefinitions: The being who has a perceptual experience, generally construed to be not on purpose.
The entity or phenomenon that the perceiver experiences with his or her senses. It is typically expressed as Object with verbs.
The <fen>Body_part</fen> is the location on the body where the perceptual experience  takes place.  It is typically expressed in a PP.
The <fen>Time</fen>, generally construed as punctual, at which the <fen>Perceiver</fen> or the <fen>Body_part</fen> perceives the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.

The <fen>Participant</fen> is either an active participant in all of the <fen>Events</fen> (e.g., Agent or Patient), or is more peripherally associated with the <fen>Events</fen> (e.g., Location or Topic).
The <fen>Events</fen> which the <fen>Participant</fen> is a part of. This role is used to mark the frame-evoking element.
When the <fen>Events</fen> concerning the <fen>Participant</fen> occured.
The <fen>Impactee</fen> is the entity which is hit by the <fen>Impactor</fen>.
The <fen>Impactor</fen> is the entity that hits the <fen>Impactee</fen> because of the <fen>Agent</fen>'s efforts.
The <fen>Impactors</fen> are the multiple entities that collide.
The <fen>Agent</fen>  causes an impact.

The <fen>Cause</fen> marks expressions that indicate some non-intentional, 
typically non-human, force that causes an <fen>Impactor</fen> to make sudden, 
forcible contact with an Impactee.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen>  when the impact occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The thing that the <fen>Perceiver</fen> is able to see or recognize.
A temporal description of the event of the <fen>Entity</fen> becoming visible.
The physical location in which the <fen>Entity</fen> becomes visible.
The <fen>Entity</fen> whose existence at the <fen>Location</fen> is confirmed.
The <fen>Location</fen> of the <fen>Entity</fen>. The <fen>Location</fen> is conceived as a ground for an event of inspection to determine the presense of the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Entity</fen> is present at the <fen>Location</fen>.
An object or event that is described as being available under delimited Conditions.
A temporal characterization of the circumstances of the existence of an <fen>Entity</fen>.
A spacial characterization of the <fex name=''>Circumstances</fex> of the existence of the <fex name=''>Entity</fex>.
A description of the state of the world in which the <fen>Entity</fen> can be experienced.
listRoleExamples: When she looked back, <fex>Maria</fex> glimpsed an arm clawing around the corner.
The waiter glimpsed <fex>a fly</fex> disappearing under the surface of the soup.
Mata Hari turned to her lawyer as <fex>her eyes</fex> glimpsed the blindfold.
We've been worried about <fex>our recent hire's</fex> history of deceiving employers.
We will focus on events in her recent <fex>history</fex>.
What I want to know is who smacked <fex>my head</fex> with a 10-ton truck?
Those hoodlums strike my car <fex>with water balloons</fex> every day!
Mr. Addams likes to collide <fex>toy trains</fex> at high speed.
<fex>One juggler</fex> was hitting the ceiling with every other ball.
A postman rammed his Fiat Panda into a getaway car <fex>after spotting the burglars </fex> .
Father Shanahan , of Rushey Mead , Leicester , rammed his Datsun into another car <fex>on the way to the city 's Gilroes cemetery</fex>.
